title: GIRLS SWIMMING: Pal-Mac caps off regular season with win
text:
GIRLS SOCCER: Panthers edge Midlakes Times Sports Staff   
GENEVA — The Geneva girls soccer team extended a late-season winning streak to four courtesy of a memorable goal from sophomore Sydney Mittiga Wednesday. 
Mittiga launched a high-arching shot from 30 yards out inside the far left post in the 60th minute to fuel the Panthers’ 1-0 Finger Lakes Central win over Midlakes. 
Nya Clark assisted on the score for the Panthers (8-7-1, 4-5-1). 
Geneva goalkeeper Sarah Bonsu hauled in eight saves. 
Jen Maslyn made four saves for the Screaming Eagles (3-12, 3-7). 
Waterloo 1, Marcus Whitman 0 
WATERLOO — Cassandra Bennett scored the game-winner with 30 seconds remaining on a cross from Malissa Temple. 
Brianna Hendrix registered 11 saves in goal for the Indians (3-13, 3-7). Katrina Meyer collected 11 saves for the Wildcats (4-11, 2-8). 
FINGER LAKES WEST 
South Seneca 7, Honeoye 3 
OVID — The Falcons (13-1, 9-0) wrapped up sole possession of their first league title behind four goals from Jenna McDonald. 
South Seneca ’keeper Morgan McGonigal snared five saves. 
Red Jacket 3, HAC 2 
SHORTSVILLE — The Indians (5-9, 5-4) erased a 2-0 halftime deficit with three second-half goals, all off the foot of Sara VanAken. 
Alexis Gardner, Sophie Busch, Rylee North supplied assists. Goalkeeper Olivia Spencer corralled 15 saves for Red Jacket (5-9, 5-4). 
Dundee 3, Romulus 0 
DUNDEE — Tayler Morrison delivered all three goals for the Scots (5-9, 3-7). Madison Hill set up two, while Emily Oughterson earned an assist on the other. 
Winning goalkeeper Andi Wood stopped four shots on goal. Emma Voorhees made 12 saves for the Warriors (1-13, 0-10).
